<p>Afferent provides fundamental types for 2D graphics: points, rectangles, sizes, colors, paths, and transforms.
These types form the foundation for all drawing operations.</p>

<h3>Point</h3>

<p>A 2D coordinate with x and y components:</p>

<pre><code class="language-lean">-- Create points
let origin := Point.mk 0.0 0.0
let position := Point.mk 100.0 50.0

-- Point operations
let offset := Point.mk 10.0 20.0
let moved := position.add offset
let distance := position.distance origin</code></pre>

<h3>Rect</h3>

<p>An axis-aligned rectangle defined by origin and size:</p>

<pre><code class="language-lean">-- Create rectangles
let bounds := Rect.mk 10.0 20.0 200.0 100.0  -- x, y, width, height
let centered := Rect.centered 400.0 300.0 100.0 50.0  -- center, size

-- Rectangle operations
let contains := bounds.contains (Point.mk 50.0 50.0)
let expanded := bounds.inset (-10.0)  -- grow by 10
let intersection := bounds.intersect otherRect</code></pre>

<h3>Size</h3>

<p>Dimensions with width and height:</p>

<pre><code class="language-lean">let windowSize := Size.mk 800.0 600.0
let area := windowSize.width * windowSize.height</code></pre>

<h3>Color</h3>

<p>RGBA color with values from 0.0 to 1.0. Afferent uses the Tincture color library:</p>

<pre><code class="language-lean">-- RGB colors (alpha defaults to 1.0)
let red := Color.rgb 1.0 0.0 0.0
let semiTransparent := Color.rgba 0.2 0.4 0.8 0.5

-- Named colors from Tincture
let bg := Color.darkSlateGray
let accent := Color.cornflowerBlue
let text := Color.white

-- HSV/HSL color spaces
let hue := Color.hsv 0.6 0.8 1.0      -- hue, saturation, value
let pastel := Color.hsl 0.3 0.5 0.8   -- hue, saturation, lightness

-- Color operations
let lighter := color.lighten 0.2
let darker := color.darken 0.1
let blended := color1.lerp color2 0.5</code></pre>

<h3>Path</h3>

<p>A sequence of drawing commands for complex shapes:</p>

<pre><code class="language-lean">-- Build a path
let path := Path.empty
  |>.moveTo 0.0 0.0
  |>.lineTo 100.0 0.0
  |>.lineTo 50.0 86.6
  |>.close  -- close back to start

-- Use in Canvas
Canvas.setFillColor Color.red
Canvas.fillPath path</code></pre>

<h3>Transform</h3>

<p>A 2D affine transformation matrix for translating, rotating, and scaling:</p>

<pre><code class="language-lean">-- Create transforms
let translate := Transform.translation 100.0 50.0
let rotate := Transform.rotation (Float.pi / 4)  -- 45 degrees
let scale := Transform.scaling 2.0 2.0

-- Combine transforms (applied right to left)
let combined := translate.concat rotate |>.concat scale

-- Transform a point
let transformed := combined.apply (Point.mk 10.0 10.0)</code></pre>

<h3>EdgeInsets</h3>

<p>Padding/margin values for all four edges:</p>

<pre><code class="language-lean">-- Uniform insets
let padding := EdgeInsets.all 10.0

-- Symmetric insets
let margins := EdgeInsets.symmetric 20.0 10.0  -- horizontal, vertical

-- Individual edges
let custom := EdgeInsets.mk 5.0 10.0 15.0 20.0  -- top, right, bottom, left</code></pre>

